      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Fair enough,  terminate is effectively noisy, but given terminate would be called if the exception were uncaught, ironically, this now makes errors which would have previously been blanket-caught via `catch(...)` etc a `terminate` which is a potentially problematic behavior change. But maybe I'm wrong on that? It was called out on me here relative to converting `assert`s to `throw`: #13268\r\n\r\nFTR I don't like that we have blanket-catches in the codebase, but they're sometimes warranted.",
